  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Give safe water to 20 slum-dwelling families</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">There are 10,000-20,000 people at any given time living in the Katanga Slum in Kampala Uganda. Each water source- a dirty community tap, a polluted spring, or the contaminated city &apos;river- makes people very sick and prevent them from going to school, working, being productive citizens, or even, living. We install filters in Katanga that last over 10 years and empower people to manage their family&apos;s health.</narrative>
  </description>
